28:21.825 --> 28:27.705
But for him it's like, it's his last
opportunity to tell people

28:27.872 --> 28:32.251
that he was never an informant,
that our federal government

28:32.460 --> 28:37.381
is more corrupt in law enforcement
than anyone ever imagined,

28:37.549 --> 28:41.969
even to this day in this trial,
it's corrupt,

28:42.137 --> 28:44.513
and he wants people to know it.

28:44.764 --> 28:46.932
There's a lot of things
that we need to dispel.

28:47.100 --> 28:50.644
The fact that Jim wasn't an informant.
l mean, the local thinking

28:50.854 --> 28:53.439
is that absolutely he was an informant.
Everybody talks about it,

28:53.606 --> 28:54.940
books are written about it.

28:55.150 --> 28:56.817
Until you actually
go through everything

28:56.985 --> 29:00.112
and look at it to make your own
independent assessment,

29:00.280 --> 29:03.574
you can't have an opinion.
So getting involved in this case,

29:03.825 --> 29:06.577
l had an opportunity that l don't
think anybody in the public does,

29:06.745 --> 29:10.205
is l get to see the files
that the government had

29:10.457 --> 29:13.834
to suggest that he was an informant.
l thought that there were some things

29:14.043 --> 29:16.003
about the file
that were so suspicious,

29:16.129 --> 29:19.757
that l wanted to look into it in depth.
And so l sat down with Daryl,

29:19.924 --> 29:22.217
and l asked her to come up with
an independent assessment,

29:22.385 --> 29:24.762
whether or not she thought there
was any legitimacy to the files.

29:24.929 --> 29:27.473
Of course l was eager to start
the project and see what l could find,

29:27.640 --> 29:30.768
but l was also a bit skeptical.
l mean, just looking at the file

29:30.935 --> 29:32.603
when it was handed to me,
l thought, how could that

29:32.729 --> 29:35.939
possibly be fictitious?
lt's 700 pages and it looks

29:36.065 --> 29:39.276
very official, so it seems like
it had to be solid.

29:39.486 --> 29:44.072
But slowly, l found a lot of
strange repetition in the file.

29:44.240 --> 29:48.368
What l've done is created tabs
on every page where l found

29:48.578 --> 29:51.872
alternate sources for the information.
And we learned that John Connolly

29:52.081 --> 29:56.001
was pilfering through files.
And Connolly took specific information

29:56.169 --> 29:58.670
from these sources,
and placed it into Mr. Bulger's file.

29:58.880 --> 30:00.672
These alternate sources
comes from wiretaps,

30:00.840 --> 30:04.468
it comes from phone calls,
news articles, public information,

30:04.677 --> 30:07.513
FBl memorandums.
And the majority of the information

30:07.680 --> 30:10.474
comes from other informant files.
A top echelon file

30:10.683 --> 30:13.977
is supposed to be filled
with singular, unique information

30:14.145 --> 30:17.105
that can lead to a prosecution.
And just based on the patterns

30:17.273 --> 30:20.150
that l found looking at
other alternate sources,

30:20.318 --> 30:23.904
it's just not consistent with someone
who was providing unique information.

30:24.072 --> 30:28.450
Like this first page of his file,
from May 29, 1981 .

30:29.994 --> 30:33.956
The tip reads that "1544 advised
that the Mafia whacked out a guy

30:34.123 --> 30:36.542
several weeks ago...
He's in the trunk of a car."

30:36.709 --> 30:38.752
lt doesn't tell
who whacked out the guy,

30:38.920 --> 30:40.295
it doesn't tell what guy
was whacked out,

30:40.463 --> 30:42.881
it doesn't tell where the car is,
there's no substantive information

30:43.132 --> 30:46.093
in that, and there's no follow-up
in the entire file.

30:46.261 --> 30:50.848
You turn, it's actually the last page,
June 8 of that same year,

30:51.015 --> 30:55.018
the same exact tip shows up.
"1544 advised that source heard

30:55.186 --> 30:57.521
that the outfit people whacked out
a guy several weeks ago

30:57.689 --> 31:01.400
and left the individual in the trunk."
lt's vague, there's no details,

31:01.651 --> 31:03.402
and it shows up twice in his file.

31:05.321 --> 31:11.201
This is not unusual to see reports
in one informant's file

31:11.369 --> 31:14.746
that's similar to reports
in another informant's file.

31:14.914 --> 31:20.002
lf a crime occurs, a law-enforcement
agency surveys their informants.

31:20.169 --> 31:23.964
They get multiple reports
from various informants

31:24.132 --> 31:25.507
about the same criminal activity.

31:25.675 --> 31:29.761
That's exactly what Connolly
was doing with Bulger.

31:29.929 --> 31:33.265
The federal government
is so desperate in this trial

31:33.474 --> 31:36.226
to try to convince people
that he's an informant.

31:36.436 --> 31:41.773
Because James Bulger had such
a strong and influential reputation,

31:41.941 --> 31:46.028
his name had value as a commodity
for the Department of Justice.

31:46.195 --> 31:49.698
They needed search warrants
to take down the Mafia.

31:49.866 --> 31:52.993
They needed to put something
down to justify intrusions

31:53.161 --> 31:54.828
into people's civil liberties.

31:55.038 --> 31:58.040
Nobody was going to look and see
if the information was verified.

31:58.166 --> 32:01.084
No one was going to determine
whether it was made up by a street agent.

32:01.210 --> 32:03.253
No one was going to determine
whether it was true or not.

32:03.504 --> 32:06.423
lt wasn't enough simply for a magistrate
to sign off on probable cause.

32:06.591 --> 32:09.801
And there is example after example
in this case

32:10.011 --> 32:14.181
of where they took James Bulger's
name and used it as a commodity.

32:14.974 --> 32:19.811
lt's a preposterous assertion that he
was not an FBl informant.

32:20.021 --> 32:24.608
ln fact, he used the FBl,
and they used him.

32:24.776 --> 32:29.780
What this is all about,
quite frankly, is he doesn't mind

32:29.948 --> 32:32.783
being called a murderer,
he doesn't mind being called

32:32.951 --> 32:36.495
a criminal, obviously he doesn't mind
being called a drug dealer,

32:36.663 --> 32:38.705
but he doesn't want to be called
an informant.

32:38.915 --> 32:43.502
Because where he came from in Southie,
that's the worst thing you can be.

32:43.670 --> 32:46.004
You can be a crook,
you can be a murderer,

32:46.214 --> 32:50.258
but it's worse to be an informant.
That's the way he's brought up,

32:50.426 --> 32:55.055
in his sick mind,
that's what he believes.

32:55.640 --> 32:59.351
The fact that the file
is 700 pages, quite frankly,

32:59.560 --> 33:05.190
that's a large file. Bulger had
this relationship for 15 or 20 years.

33:08.152 --> 33:11.822
When they were saying that
he had a voluminous FBl file,

33:12.073 --> 33:14.616
how long were they claiming
that he was an FBl informant?

33:15.994 --> 33:17.119
Almost 20 years.

33:17.286 --> 33:19.955
Okay.
Well, l have extensive experience

33:20.164 --> 33:21.832
with a lot of informant files,

33:22.000 --> 33:27.629
and a top echelon informant file
is never going to be 700 pages.

33:27.839 --> 33:30.382
What should, generally,
the size of the file be?

33:30.550 --> 33:32.551
For 20 years?

33:32.844 --> 33:37.889
Anywhere from 60,000,

33:37.974 --> 33:43.145
55,000, up to,
you know, 300,000.

33:44.230 --> 33:46.565
The problem with the top echelon
informant program,

33:46.733 --> 33:49.067
it's not unique to the Bulger case,

33:49.235 --> 33:51.319
and a lot of people are dying
because of it.

33:51.446 --> 33:55.782
So l file a Freedom of lnformation Act
lawsuit against the government,

33:55.992 --> 33:57.993
and l won massive files,

33:58.202 --> 34:01.747
55,000 pages of files just on
one top echelon informant,

34:01.914 --> 34:05.959
Gregory Scarpa, a high level
informant for the FBl in New York.

34:06.127 --> 34:09.629
His main role was to
bring down the Colombo crime family.

34:09.797 --> 34:12.591
But at the same time,
he was lying and killing off

34:12.759 --> 34:16.053
his rivals and committing murders,
a lot of murders.

34:16.219 --> 34:18.429
ln trial, they said
more than 50 people.

34:20.016 --> 34:22.768
l don't know if you've ever seen
a real informant file or not.

34:22.976 --> 34:25.520
- l haven't. That looks heavy.
- Because l don't think that you have.

34:25.646 --> 34:28.190
See, you didn't have this
on yours, correct?

34:28.357 --> 34:32.277
These are important, these are
showing who these went to

34:32.487 --> 34:33.820
and who authorized these.

34:33.946 --> 34:35.614
That's an unbelievable
amount of signatures.

34:35.739 --> 34:36.697
Exactly.

34:36.824 --> 34:38.949
That means everybody here
saw this or endorsed it.

34:39.118 --> 34:43.246
Yeah, exactly.
And, but look how high it went up.

34:43.331 --> 34:46.333
Kelly, Deloach, that's up there,
that's up there with,

34:46.501 --> 34:48.335
with Hoover.

34:48.460 --> 34:52.089
And then it should go into
the information that he provided.

34:52.255 --> 34:57.219
He's given information, and then
the FBl does their own summary.

34:57.386 --> 35:00.055
Here. "This informant has not
furnished any information

35:00.139 --> 35:02.891
known to be false."
Do you have any of that on yours?

35:03.017 --> 35:04.309
We don't have things like that.

35:04.477 --> 35:08.688
And this is a total of 1147 pages.

35:08.856 --> 35:11.149
So, and that's just the first set.

35:11.400 --> 35:14.402
Now, l have an additional 55 coming,

35:14.612 --> 35:16.238
55,000 coming.

35:17.907 --> 35:21.743
Remember the day when Hank and l
were with you, and showed you

35:21.953 --> 35:25.997
the so-called informant file
that John Connolly had been keeping?

35:26.124 --> 35:27.082
Yeah.

35:27.208 --> 35:29.417
Remember your reaction
to seeing that?

35:29.585 --> 35:33.672
l was shocked. l was angry.
l couldn't believe it was,

35:33.840 --> 35:37.634
l consider it the worst betrayal that ever,
ever happened to me in my life.

35:37.802 --> 35:41.346
l couldn't believe that anyone
even could dream of such a thing.

35:41.514 --> 35:43.181
l never knew it existed.

35:43.349 --> 35:46.476
Did you recognize the information
that was contained in it

35:46.644 --> 35:49.146
as anything that you would
ever talk to John Connolly about?

35:49.313 --> 35:52.399
No. l asked the questions,
l got the answers.

35:52.567 --> 35:55.694
l was the guy who did the directing,
they didn't direct me.

35:55.862 --> 35:58.029
What are some of the things
they would give you

35:58.197 --> 35:59.531
in terms of tips?

35:59.699 --> 36:03.493
The thing that we needed most
of, number one, was wiretaps.

36:03.703 --> 36:06.705
And then, like, photo surveillance,
search warrants

36:06.873 --> 36:09.082
when they were coming,
indictments that were coming,

36:09.250 --> 36:11.918
so guys could get a chance
to make a run for it.

36:12.044 --> 36:15.172
Well, if you weren't providing
information to these people,

36:15.339 --> 36:18.508
why were they willing to give you
all this information?

36:18.676 --> 36:22.345
For money, for money.
Money's the common denominator.

36:22.597 --> 36:24.973
lt's a way of doing business.
lt happens all the time,

36:25.141 --> 36:26.808
it'll never stop.

36:26.976 --> 36:29.853
l remember you told me once
that Christmas

36:29.979 --> 36:32.355
- is for kids and cops.
- Correct.

36:32.565 --> 36:36.902
How many people would you be
paying off on a holiday period?

36:37.069 --> 36:40.238
Everybody l knew l took care of
at Christmas time.

36:40.448 --> 36:44.743
Put money in envelopes for all of
the different police. l had contacts

36:44.994 --> 36:48.872
on the state police,
the Boston police, the ATF,

36:49.040 --> 36:52.250
also in the FBl. There was more people
than John Connolly, but l'm not going

36:52.418 --> 36:56.046
to say who they were. l would
never say anybody's name, you know.

36:56.214 --> 36:57.797
But l took care of everybody.

36:57.965 --> 36:59.549
And was this in cash?

36:59.717 --> 37:03.428
Always cash.
l never handed anyone money,

37:03.596 --> 37:04.930
l handed them an envelope,

37:05.097 --> 37:08.308
makes it a little bit easier for them
to accept it, you know?

37:08.476 --> 37:12.145
Or l put the money maybe in a box,
if it was that much money.

37:12.313 --> 37:17.400
What was the most amount of money
you ever paid an FBl person, FBl agent?

37:17.568 --> 37:20.070
-At one time?
-Yeah.

37:20.238 --> 37:23.448
l don't know,
maybe 25,000, 50,000.

37:25.034 --> 37:28.411
Everybody can be corrupted.
People who are of the opinion

37:28.579 --> 37:31.831
that the FBl is above reproach...

37:32.583 --> 37:34.334
Well, they're just regular people.

37:34.460 --> 37:37.254
They put their pants on in the morning
just like everybody else.

37:37.463 --> 37:38.755
They are regular people,

37:38.881 --> 37:42.342
except they have a badge that says,
you know, "Special Agent."

37:42.551 --> 37:45.971
But there's nothing special
about them, they are regular people.

37:46.138 --> 37:49.724
lf you find their weakness, or their needs,
or if they have a problem

37:49.892 --> 37:53.186
and you can solve it for them,
you can corrupt them.

37:53.354 --> 37:56.314
Maybe they like money, maybe
they like wine, maybe they like jewelry,

37:56.482 --> 37:58.358
you know, trips, whatever.

37:58.484 --> 38:01.069
There's always a way
to corrupt somebody.

38:01.237 --> 38:05.240
Man: During a rapid-fire and sometimes
intense cross-examination,

38:05.449 --> 38:07.951
disgraced former FBl supervisor
John Morris

38:08.119 --> 38:10.829
admitted taking thousands
in cash from Bulger.

38:10.997 --> 38:14.916
Man 2: Mr. Morris, you were Mr. Bulger's
paid FBl informant, weren't you?

38:15.084 --> 38:17.377
Morris: That's not correct.
He did give me money,

38:17.545 --> 38:19.170
but l was not his paid informant.

38:19.338 --> 38:20.547
- Man 2: Gave you money?
- Morris: Yes.

38:20.673 --> 38:21.798
- Man 2: Gave you gifts?
- Morris: Yes.

38:21.966 --> 38:23.883
Man 2: You got a case of wine,
didn't you, from Mr. Connolly

38:24.051 --> 38:25.844
- in the basement of the federal office?
- Morris: That's correct.

38:26.012 --> 38:28.555
- Man 2: Did you throw it away?
- Morris: No, l kept it.

38:32.476 --> 38:35.353
You know, seeing a day
like today where, it's not clear,

38:35.479 --> 38:39.607
you see, you see thoroughly,
despicably corrupt FBl agents

38:39.775 --> 38:45.155
like John Morris, a supervisor.
You know, with just a moral...

38:47.033 --> 38:48.533
l mean, he was a moral coward.

38:48.701 --> 38:49.617
Boeri: And you see him,

38:49.785 --> 38:53.913
and you see Connolly taking advantage
of him in all his weakness,

38:54.081 --> 38:56.833
to bring him into the group.

38:57.001 --> 38:58.960
You see that, and you see
what was allowed.

38:59.128 --> 39:02.422
And so, the real story here,
is that our government

39:02.590 --> 39:07.218
enabled killers to run free
in this city, you know?

39:07.386 --> 39:09.512
Bulger used to wake up
in South Boston,

39:09.638 --> 39:11.514
and from South Boston
you can look across,

39:11.682 --> 39:14.851
and he would say, "l own that town."
And he really did.

39:15.019 --> 39:18.396
And he owned it because,
he was allowed to turn

39:18.564 --> 39:23.026
the Federal Bureau of lnvestigation into
the Bulger Bureau of lnvestigation.

39:23.194 --> 39:27.364
He put his tentacles into the Bureau
and he turned it into something

39:27.490 --> 39:30.325
that worked for him.
And it was because they were all

39:30.493 --> 39:35.955
crazed about getting the Mafia,
that they enabled the lrish Godfather

39:36.082 --> 39:37.582
to run the show here.

39:37.750 --> 39:40.877
And he was far more dangerous
than the ltalians.

39:45.633 --> 39:48.468
So what we need to do is get inside
a little bit and talk about

39:48.594 --> 39:51.930
how the FBl works,
what the roles of certain people were

39:52.098 --> 39:56.142
like Mr. Connolly and Mr. Morris.
And the more we can

39:56.310 --> 39:59.145
keep you on the stand,
from my perspective the better,

39:59.313 --> 40:02.690
because hopefully, it will be able to
really illustrate the effort you made,

40:02.858 --> 40:05.318
so they see the good side
of law enforcement.

40:05.486 --> 40:08.530
You recognized it was a problem, you
tried to do something to save lives,

40:08.697 --> 40:11.157
and because they were
pursuing whatever agenda they were,

40:11.242 --> 40:13.368
- they shut you down.
- Can l be candid with you?

40:13.536 --> 40:15.412
l think the whole thing was a con.

40:15.579 --> 40:18.915
l think at some point
they get in over their heads,

40:19.041 --> 40:24.963
and their success was wrapped
around Bulger, to the point where he

40:25.131 --> 40:26.423
had to be validated,

40:26.590 --> 40:31.344
he had to be made
into this informant

40:31.554 --> 40:33.680
that gave them all this information.

40:33.848 --> 40:34.848
Brennan: That's the myth.

40:34.974 --> 40:36.391
That's the myth.

40:37.059 --> 40:40.770
Fitzpatrick: l had a fascinating career.
l worked organized crime,

40:40.938 --> 40:44.858
l worked fugitives.
And in Mississippi, l had to work

40:45.025 --> 40:46.985
the Ku Klux Klan, bombings.

40:47.153 --> 40:50.738
And we ended
the bombings in Mississippi.

40:50.906 --> 40:53.408
Then l was
transferred back to Memphis.

40:54.535 --> 40:57.287
Martin Luther King came to Memphis
and l was told

40:57.455 --> 40:59.330
that King had just been shot.

41:00.749 --> 41:03.376
We found the gun
and through the fingerprints

41:03.502 --> 41:07.672
we identified James Earl Ray,
and we arrested him in London.

41:07.882 --> 41:12.427
ln Miami, we developed a case
called ABSCAM.

41:12.553 --> 41:17.140
ABSCAM turned out to be one of the
largest white-collar crime cases ever.

41:17.349 --> 41:21.019
And we arrested senators,
a sitting senator.

41:21.228 --> 41:26.608
So when l went back to headquarters,
and the Boston problem was going on,

41:26.775 --> 41:29.486
l was told they needed somebody
with this background

41:29.612 --> 41:35.074
to be sent to Boston. And my mission
was to find out what is going on

41:35.242 --> 41:38.786
between the Mass State Police,
the Boston Police,

41:38.954 --> 41:40.580
the local police, and the FBl,

41:40.748 --> 41:42.832
and how come they're not
getting along together.

41:43.000 --> 41:44.667
They had territorial issues.

41:44.919 --> 41:49.464
The state police was blaming the FBl
for cavorting with criminals,

41:49.632 --> 41:56.095
because they had seen Connolly and
Morris with Bulger and Flemmi.

41:56.639 --> 42:01.226
So they formed the opinion that the
agents were doing something bad.

42:01.393 --> 42:03.978
Well, as it turned out, they were.

42:04.146 --> 42:07.148
But they didn't know it then,
and l didn't know it then.

42:07.316 --> 42:11.027
So l go out and interview Bulger

42:11.195 --> 42:15.365
and assess him, a suitability,
if you will.

42:15.533 --> 42:20.578
l arrive at Bulger's place,
and met at the door by Bulger.

42:20.746 --> 42:21.955
He's got a baseball cap on,

42:22.122 --> 42:24.791
he's got sunglasses,
he's got a muscle shirt.

42:24.959 --> 42:28.294
l hold out my paw, my hand,
and he doesn't take it.

42:28.462 --> 42:33.841
Okay, you know. So l look at my
empty hand and l follow him in.

42:34.009 --> 42:39.931
The place is dark. And we walk
in the back. l say, "Look, Bulger,

42:40.182 --> 42:43.184
l'm here to find out what
you're doing for us.

42:43.352 --> 42:45.144
What are you doing for us?"

42:45.563 --> 42:51.484
And he gets angry. And about
that time, Connolly pops out.

42:51.819 --> 42:54.445
And remember this was supposed to be
mano a mano, one-on-one.

42:54.822 --> 43:00.368
And l get very angry. And l look over
and he says, "Hi, Fitzy, how you doing?"

43:00.744 --> 43:05.832
And l'm saying to myself, "Oh,"
you know, "this does not look good."

43:05.958 --> 43:09.294
But then we have
the conversation about him.

43:09.461 --> 43:11.421
l finally get the conversation back.

43:11.589 --> 43:14.674
And what he tells me is that
he's not an informant,

43:14.967 --> 43:20.847
that he has his own informants, and that
he pays them, they don't pay him,

43:21.098 --> 43:25.226
and that he's the head of a gang,
and that he runs the gang,

43:25.394 --> 43:29.314
that he's not going to testify.
Now all those elements

43:29.481 --> 43:33.776
are elements to me that l'm going to
close this guy as an informant.

43:33.944 --> 43:36.738
lf you're an informant for the FBl
and you're the head of the gang,

43:36.905 --> 43:39.991
then the FBl is validating the gang.

43:40.242 --> 43:43.911
You're actually part of the gang
and the management process.

43:44.079 --> 43:46.748
So to me, he's a big problem.

43:46.915 --> 43:50.084
Close him, get rid of him.
And that's what l go back

43:50.252 --> 43:51.669
and tell my boss.

43:51.837 --> 43:54.505
From that point on,
l get resistance.

43:54.673 --> 43:57.216
l'm more or less told, "You shut up.

43:57.384 --> 43:58.843
You're not allowed
to talk about this."

44:02.473 --> 44:04.265
Murphy: l was a very young reporter,

44:04.350 --> 44:09.145
but l had covered this huge Mafia trial
in Boston, it was the biggest ever.

44:09.313 --> 44:13.524
lt was, um... The FBl had planted a bug
in the north end headquarters

44:13.692 --> 44:15.234
of a guy named Jerry Angiulo.

44:15.402 --> 44:17.654
He was the underboss
of the Mafia,

44:17.821 --> 44:20.698
and ran everything in Boston.
And he and his brothers,

44:20.866 --> 44:23.951
the whole hierarchy went on trial,
it was an eight month trial.

44:25.287 --> 44:29.415
And there was all this evidence
of murders, and corruption,

44:29.583 --> 44:33.586
and they had tapes of Jerry Angiulo
bragging about murders.

44:33.754 --> 44:37.131
But they also had him talking about,
"l have a couple of guys

44:37.299 --> 44:39.926
that will do anything for us
named Whitey and Stevie,

44:40.052 --> 44:42.637
they'll kill anyone we ask them to."

44:42.805 --> 44:45.390
And so at the end of that trial,
it was a huge victory

44:45.557 --> 44:48.184
for the FBl in Boston.
They had just wiped out

44:48.352 --> 44:50.978
the New England family,
decimated them.

44:51.146 --> 44:54.982
Yesterday, a federal grand jury
sitting at Boston

44:55.150 --> 44:59.195
returned a 20 count indictment
charging seven individuals,

44:59.405 --> 45:01.322
including Gennaro Angiulo.

45:01.490 --> 45:04.409
Murphy: The Boston FBl,
they were heroes, and John Connolly

45:04.576 --> 45:08.413
was at the heart of that, he was
the guy with the most informants

45:08.539 --> 45:11.249
the most top echelon informants.

45:11.834 --> 45:14.794
So as the Mafia is being decimated,

45:14.962 --> 45:18.506
stepping into the vacuum
are Whitey Bulger and Steve Flemmi.

45:18.757 --> 45:22.427
And l'm asking the New England
strike force leader, Jerry O'Sullivan,

45:22.636 --> 45:25.513
why aren't you
going after Whitey and Stevie?

45:25.764 --> 45:29.142
You've already done the Mafia
repeatedly, what about these guys?

45:29.309 --> 45:32.228
And the answer is, "Oh, well,
they're not the threat

45:32.396 --> 45:36.482
that the Mafia is, the Mafia
is an international organization,

45:36.650 --> 45:37.775
Whitey's this local hoodlum.

45:37.943 --> 45:40.027
We're the New England
Organized Crime Strike Force,

45:40.195 --> 45:41.821
we go after the big guys."

45:42.072 --> 45:44.991
Well, Whitey was
becoming the big fish.

45:51.832 --> 45:57.003
Carney: Jim Bulger wants to explain
to the jury why for 25 years

45:57.129 --> 46:02.258
he could be on top of the organized
crime pyramid in Boston,

46:02.426 --> 46:05.011
and never once be charged
with a crime.

46:05.179 --> 46:10.808
The chief of the Organized Crime
Strike Force, Jeremiah O'Sullivan,

46:10.976 --> 46:16.397
promised him that he would not be
prosecuted for any federal crime,

46:16.565 --> 46:22.111
if in turn, he did something
that the government wanted.

46:23.155 --> 46:25.782
And that something
was not being an informant,

46:25.949 --> 46:27.617
it was something else.

46:27.743 --> 46:30.787
We've never revealed that information,

46:30.954 --> 46:34.457
but Jim will at trial,
if Jim takes the stand.

46:35.793 --> 46:39.003
Bulger: l had met secretly
with a high official

46:39.213 --> 46:42.965
in the federal strike force,
Jerry O'Sullivan, United States Attorney.

46:43.133 --> 46:45.384
He was concerned that someone
was going to kill him.

46:45.552 --> 46:48.012
He says that he's in trouble,
and he needs help.

46:48.180 --> 46:50.640
l felt bad for him, so l told him,

46:50.766 --> 46:53.893
l says, "Look, l'll take care of this
for you, but l'm no spy.

46:54.102 --> 46:56.729
We don't meet, l'll take care of it
my own way.

46:56.897 --> 46:58.523
lf you can accept that,
it'll be done."

46:58.690 --> 47:01.317
Carney: What was O'Sullivan's
promise to you?

47:01.485 --> 47:04.195
His promise to me was this.
He says, "Listen, Whitey,"

47:04.321 --> 47:07.865
he says, "l feel better, l'm under
your umbrella of protection,

47:08.033 --> 47:12.245
you're under mine," and he says,
"Any federal crimes or anything like that,

47:12.412 --> 47:15.206
don't worry about it." He says,
"l'll always be in your corner

47:15.374 --> 47:18.835
from this point on.
l'll protect you, you protect me."

47:19.002 --> 47:20.545
And that was the way it went.

47:22.422 --> 47:28.302
Bulger claims that he had
saved Jeremiah T. O'Sullivan

47:29.304 --> 47:35.226
from imminent danger,
presumably from Mafia retaliation

47:35.394 --> 47:40.231
for Jeremiah O'Sullivan's pursuit
of the Mafia and bringing it down,

47:40.399 --> 47:44.777
and that his deal with Jeremiah
T. O'Sullivan was a personal one,

47:44.945 --> 47:48.698
and he was going to
protect O'Sullivan in return

47:48.866 --> 47:54.161
for being granted immunity
for crimes past and future.

47:55.414 --> 47:58.958
John Connolly said that O'Sullivan
and Bulger pledged allegiance

47:59.084 --> 48:03.170
to each other.
That's a pretty significant event,

48:03.338 --> 48:06.799
an event by the way that was never
mentioned or even alluded to

48:06.967 --> 48:09.760
in this trial. The government
didn't want it to be,

48:09.970 --> 48:13.848
because then you would have
this very ironic situation

48:14.016 --> 48:17.602
of the US Attorney's Office in Boston,
the very office

48:17.769 --> 48:20.855
that is currently prosecuting
Whitey Bulger, had some kind of

48:21.064 --> 48:23.065
corrupt relationship with Whitey Bulger,

48:23.233 --> 48:25.484
that they're not being
totally forthcoming about.

48:26.778 --> 48:32.241
The notion that a federal prosecutor
could tell an organized crime figure

48:32.409 --> 48:34.952
that he could kill at will,
men and women,

48:35.120 --> 48:38.998
rich and poor,
Boston, Florida, Oklahoma,

48:39.082 --> 48:44.587
based on a personal promise
to guarantee his safety, is so absurd,

48:44.755 --> 48:50.051
so ludicrous, we've run out
of words like "ludicrous"

48:50.218 --> 48:51.844
and synonyms to describe it.

48:55.182 --> 48:58.267
Woman: Today they call to the stand
former number two

48:58.435 --> 49:02.563
in the FBl's Boston office,
Agent Bob Fitzpatrick.

49:02.731 --> 49:05.149
Fitzpatrick: Kind of upset over the fact
that this whole case

49:05.317 --> 49:09.320
is predicated on a bunch of people
l tried to put in jail,

49:09.488 --> 49:13.574
and the true story
is that the criminal justice system

49:13.700 --> 49:17.536
has basically been co-opted
by Bulger, by Flemmi.

49:17.704 --> 49:21.248
Now certain people
are culpable in the FBl,

49:21.416 --> 49:25.127
but certain people are culpable
in the Department of Justice.

49:25.212 --> 49:28.214
So l've got to go there
and present the truth.

49:28.382 --> 49:31.175
Woman: Former FBl agent
Robert Fitzpatrick

49:31.343 --> 49:35.304
started at the Boston office in 1981 ,
and said the atmosphere was tense.

49:35.472 --> 49:38.015
As Assistant Special Agent
ln Charge, Fitzpatrick

49:38.183 --> 49:41.102
evaluated James Bulger's role
as an informant.

49:41.269 --> 49:45.690
Fitzpatrick said Bulger surprised him
by saying he was not an FBl informant,

49:45.857 --> 49:49.860
that he was never paid anything
by the FBl to provide information.

49:49.987 --> 49:52.613
Fitzpatrick recommended
closing Bulger as an informant,

49:52.864 --> 49:54.490
but headquarters
thought Bulger was too valuable

49:54.658 --> 49:58.369
in its quest to bring down the Mafia.
After several hours on the stand,

49:58.537 --> 50:01.580
prosecutors began a tough
cross-examination of Fitzpatrick.

50:01.707 --> 50:02.832
First question?

50:03.000 --> 50:05.334
Kelly: You're a man who likes to
make up stories, aren't you?

50:05.377 --> 50:06.252
Fitzpatrick: No.

50:06.420 --> 50:09.005
Kelly: Didn't you gratuitously claim
credit for arresting the mob boss

50:09.172 --> 50:11.132
- Jerry Angiulo?
- Fitzpatrick: l did arrest him.

50:11.299 --> 50:13.676
Kelly: Haven't you in fact pretended
that you were the one

50:13.844 --> 50:16.178
who found the rifle that killed
Martin Luther King?

50:16.346 --> 50:18.764
Fitzpatrick: l did find the rifle,
when l was at the scene.

50:18.932 --> 50:21.058
Woman: At one point,
Assistant US Attorney Brian Kelly said,

50:21.226 --> 50:22.852
"Are you on medication?"

50:23.020 --> 50:25.938
Fitzpatrick said,
"Yes." Kelly said sarcastically,

50:26.106 --> 50:27.314
"Does it affect your memory?"

50:27.482 --> 50:29.775
"Not that l recall,"
replied Fitzpatrick,

50:29.985 --> 50:32.278
as several people in court laughed.

50:33.488 --> 50:35.197
Woman: How do you think you were
treated on the stand?

50:35.365 --> 50:36.240
Not good.

50:36.450 --> 50:37.908
What do you mean?

50:38.076 --> 50:40.661
l thought the guy was very angry,
and l don't know why.

50:40.829 --> 50:43.873
You know, it should've been
a lot more professional,

50:44.041 --> 50:47.626
and l didn't feel that professionalism.

50:47.711 --> 50:50.838
And plus, as a former law enforcement
officer working with these guys,

50:51.006 --> 50:52.381
l should have had
a little more respect.

50:52.591 --> 50:56.594
You know, l'm actually disgusted
in some sense, to be honest with you.

50:56.803 --> 50:59.180
To hear Fitzpatrick
get grilled like that,

50:59.347 --> 51:02.183
and not all the other agents?
l think it's garbage.

51:02.350 --> 51:04.727
That's the first time that
the prosecution has cross-examined

51:04.895 --> 51:06.395
anybody in that manner.

51:06.563 --> 51:08.939
Other than that, they been up there
kissing everybody's ass.

51:09.191 --> 51:12.610
All the dirty FBl agents,
all ex-mobsters.

51:12.778 --> 51:15.905
Look at Morris, they didn't treat
Morris like Fitzpatrick.

51:16.073 --> 51:17.782
These are the guys
they gave deals to.

51:17.949 --> 51:21.160
Fitzpatrick tried to go out of his way
and do the right thing,

51:21.328 --> 51:24.914
but he's still fighting for a pension.
Morris got a pension.

51:25.957 --> 51:29.210
Kelly: With respect to my
cross-examination of Fitzpatrick,

51:29.419 --> 51:32.004
l do think it was fair.
l think when people

51:32.172 --> 51:35.132
come into federal court
and tell ridiculous stories,

51:35.258 --> 51:39.470
they can expect to be confronted
aggressively with cross-examination.

51:39.554 --> 51:41.097
That's the purpose
of cross-examination,

51:41.264 --> 51:43.557
you try to expose
what isn't accurate.

51:43.725 --> 51:45.434
Now Fitzpatrick was in fact

51:45.602 --> 51:49.063
in the chain of command
at exactly the same time

51:49.231 --> 51:53.234
all this crime and buffoonery
was occurring. And yet years later,

51:53.401 --> 51:56.862
he wanted to distance himself
from it and pretend

51:56.988 --> 51:58.489
he was trying to stop it.

52:00.033 --> 52:03.119
English: Bob Fitzpatrick was one of
the first people to say

52:03.328 --> 52:06.664
there's something rotten here,
and to try to call attention to it.

52:06.832 --> 52:10.751
He's drummed out of the FBl,
now here he is at this trial,

52:10.961 --> 52:14.880
and they really seek to destroy him,
they seek to humiliate him,

52:15.048 --> 52:20.261
and it was very personal, because
when he comes in to trial to testify,

52:20.428 --> 52:23.389
he is a rebuke to the entire system

52:23.557 --> 52:26.809
and to everyone who stood back

52:26.977 --> 52:31.522
for 20 years that Bulger was in
power and allowed it to happen.

52:31.690 --> 52:35.109
And a lot of people were
complicit in that.

52:36.820 --> 52:41.365
Brennan: lt was a little bit tormenting
to watch Fitzpatrick get beat up.

52:41.533 --> 52:43.701
lt shows you that you're
either with the government,

52:43.869 --> 52:47.621
and they'll accept, and guide,
and protect you

52:47.789 --> 52:49.999
in any way they can, or you're
against the government,

52:50.167 --> 52:51.709
and they'll try to destroy you.

52:53.879 --> 52:56.505
We know that there was
a relationship between

52:56.673 --> 52:59.925
the Department of Justice and
the success of James Bulger,

53:00.093 --> 53:02.344
and nobody wants to tell that story.

53:02.512 --> 53:05.848
They protected him for
their own reasons for decades,

53:06.057 --> 53:07.766
and they're still lying about it.

53:07.934 --> 53:12.021
At this trial, the United States
Attorney's Office has an exhibit.

53:12.147 --> 53:13.564
lt's a very important exhibit.

53:13.732 --> 53:16.233
lt is a memorandum
from the Special Agent ln Charge

53:16.401 --> 53:19.028
in the 1980s by the name
of Lawrence Sarhatt.

53:19.196 --> 53:22.823
ln this memorandum, Sarhatt says
that he had a conversation

53:22.908 --> 53:27.119
with James Bulger when they met
at a hotel. And the government pretends

53:27.287 --> 53:31.415
that this memorandum somehow shows
James Bulger is an informant.

53:31.583 --> 53:34.251
So, during the trial
we learn information

53:34.502 --> 53:37.213
that there's a secret safe
in the Boston SAC,

53:37.422 --> 53:40.799
that's Special Agent in Charge's office
in the C3 unit of the FBl,

53:41.051 --> 53:45.095
the criminal division, and in that safe,
supposedly documents will go into

53:45.222 --> 53:46.555
and never come out again.

53:46.723 --> 53:49.183
We also learned
that there was a secretary

53:49.309 --> 53:53.229
who had worked for decades
in the Boston FBl.

53:53.438 --> 53:56.607
She's 82 years old, and still working
for the Boston FBl.

53:56.816 --> 54:00.694
So, she is the person who knows
whether or not a secret safe exists.

54:13.250 --> 54:15.251
Brennan: When we called
this secretary as a witness,

54:15.418 --> 54:18.420
mysteriously new documents appeared.

54:18.588 --> 54:20.339
While they told the jury
and the public

54:20.507 --> 54:23.717
- this is the truth at this trial...
- Man: At this trial.

54:23.802 --> 54:25.636
what we learned
when we called the secretary

54:25.762 --> 54:27.805
is there were other documents
that existed.

54:27.931 --> 54:31.600
The same exact memo
that the government introduced

54:31.768 --> 54:36.272
at this trial from the same person,
exact copy of it,

54:36.439 --> 54:39.400
we learned that the memo
was not complete,

54:39.567 --> 54:41.443
because there's
an observation section.

54:42.821 --> 54:45.281
Mr. Sarhatt says, "l am not certain
that l am convinced

54:45.448 --> 54:48.242
the informant is telling
the full story of his involvement.

54:48.410 --> 54:50.369
Consideration should be given
to closing him

54:50.453 --> 54:52.121
and making him a target."

54:54.082 --> 54:55.499
So what do they do
with this information?

54:55.667 --> 55:00.212
Well, the government at this trial,
leaves that part out until we expose it.

55:00.380 --> 55:03.841
What else did they do with
the information back in 1980?

55:04.009 --> 55:07.553
We'd learn from the secretary exactly
what they did with that information.

55:07.762 --> 55:10.723
The actual memorandum
that was given to her,

55:10.890 --> 55:13.642
she put in an envelope
by direction of Mr. Sarhatt,

55:13.810 --> 55:18.689
and put in the safe.
And it says, "Strictly Eyes-Only."

55:18.857 --> 55:21.984
Nobody other than the Special Agent
in Charge should see it.

55:22.152 --> 55:24.611
And anytime a new Special Agent
ln Charge would come in

55:24.779 --> 55:28.157
and take the place of an old one
who was resigning or moving on,

55:28.325 --> 55:30.367
she would tell them
about this document in the safe,

55:30.535 --> 55:32.953
and it stayed in that safe
for generations

55:33.121 --> 55:36.206
of Special Agents in Charge
when they took each other's spot.

55:37.542 --> 55:40.210
And one Special Agent ln Charge
said, "Get rid of this,

55:40.378 --> 55:42.129
or we'll all get fired."

55:44.424 --> 55:46.216
What could be so terrible
about this document

55:46.384 --> 55:49.470
that they would lose their job?
That James Bulger was an informant?

55:49.637 --> 55:51.638
Would that be so terrible
everybody would get fired?

55:51.806 --> 55:54.141
Or that they knew
he wasn't an informant,

55:54.309 --> 55:55.934
they knew that he
should've been targeted,

55:56.102 --> 55:58.187
and he was being protected.

56:03.068 --> 56:07.279
Kelly: The defense complaining
about the Sarhatt memo

56:07.447 --> 56:11.533
is another desperate tactic by them,
which is another version of,

56:11.701 --> 56:12.701
"Let's pretend,"

56:12.869 --> 56:15.913
because they are pretending
they didn't have these documents,

56:16.122 --> 56:20.292
which they did. There's nothing sinister
about it, it was disclosed.

56:20.502 --> 56:24.171
They had it. And it didn't...
it didn't prove anything,

56:24.339 --> 56:27.132
other than the fact that
there was a head of the FBl

56:27.300 --> 56:30.386
who was concerned about
keeping Bulger open as an informant.

56:30.553 --> 56:33.931
lf anything, the Sarhatt memo
proves Bulger was an informant.

56:34.099 --> 56:37.351
He sat with the head of
the Boston FBl for four hours

56:37.519 --> 56:41.188
and gave them all sorts of information,
most of which was useless,

56:41.314 --> 56:43.899
but in fact, he was
reporting it to the FBl,

56:44.067 --> 56:46.318
and that makes him an informant.

56:50.573 --> 56:54.201
Woman: The latest twist in the trial
of James Whitey Bulger.

56:54.369 --> 56:57.454
Man: On Tuesday, Stephen Rakes was
dropped from the witness list.

56:57.622 --> 57:00.833
Woman 2: Rakes had been set to testify,
but prosecutors told him he was

57:01.000 --> 57:02.876
no longer needed to
take the stand.

57:03.044 --> 57:05.796
Thirty years of torment, and
now it's coming to an end.

57:07.424 --> 57:09.466
( phone ringing )

57:09.634 --> 57:13.762
Hello. No, l haven't been
able to get...

57:13.930 --> 57:16.348
l'm going by his house later
because l haven't been able

57:16.516 --> 57:18.767
to get a hold of him or anything.

57:18.935 --> 57:23.021
Yeah, he's probably
beside himself about it.

57:23.189 --> 57:25.023
They took him off the witness list.

57:25.191 --> 57:27.484
l tried calling him after court,

57:27.652 --> 57:31.572
and his phone went right to voicemail.
l call him all day yesterday,

57:31.739 --> 57:35.909
same, after court, same thing.
So, l'm going to go over.

57:36.077 --> 57:39.621
l figure, give him
a little time to cool down.

57:39.789 --> 57:41.290
Yeah.

57:41.416 --> 57:43.917
( indistinct voice on phone )

57:44.043 --> 57:45.502
Yeah.

57:47.213 --> 57:48.714
Where?

57:49.007 --> 57:51.717
l don't know, what was
the body described like?

57:54.137 --> 57:58.140
That's him.

57:59.309 --> 58:01.018
Motherfucker.

58:02.437 --> 58:05.063
l'm going by his house right now.

58:05.231 --> 58:07.649
Yeah, l'll call you
right back, bye.

58:07.817 --> 58:08.859
- He's dead.
- Woman: He's dead?

58:09.027 --> 58:13.322
What, what?
What? What happened?

58:13.531 --> 58:16.825
They found him on
the side of the road in Lincoln.

58:16.993 --> 58:18.076
Woman: ln Lincoln, Massachusetts?

58:18.244 --> 58:18.994
Yeah.

58:19.162 --> 58:20.496
Woman: Who's in Lincoln,
Massachusetts?

58:20.663 --> 58:22.372
l gotta go by his house right now.

58:22.582 --> 58:24.708
Woman: Who's in...
Oh, my God, no way.

58:24.876 --> 58:27.961
Man: Stephen Rakes is a courthouse
regular, coming each day

58:28.171 --> 58:31.673
to the Whitey Bulger trial, waiting
for the day when he would testify,

58:31.841 --> 58:33.884
but Rakes would never
get that chance.

58:34.594 --> 58:35.844
See the corruption?

58:36.012 --> 58:38.013
Woman: Well, wait,
let's not jump to conclusions.

58:38.181 --> 58:40.140
Let's say a prayer that he's okay.

58:40.308 --> 58:42.434
- He's not here.
- Woman: Oh, my God.

58:42.644 --> 58:44.853
- Woman: ls his car here, Stephen?
- No.

58:44.979 --> 58:48.023
Woman: Oh, my God. Can you go
knock on the door and see?

58:48.191 --> 58:49.775
Davis: l knew something was wrong,

58:49.901 --> 58:52.736
because l talk to him every day,
we meet for coffee.

58:52.904 --> 58:54.488
( ringing doorbell )

58:54.614 --> 58:56.949
You know, and that's got
my stomach turned, thinking,

58:57.116 --> 58:59.701
"ls anyone else in danger?"

58:59.869 --> 59:02.329
With his testimony,
l used to say to him,

59:02.497 --> 59:04.623
"Steve, what do you have to say?
l mean, what is it?"

59:04.791 --> 59:07.251
"Oh, you'll see, you'll see.

59:07.377 --> 59:11.338
Believe me, you'll see how deep
the people... you'll see."

59:11.464 --> 59:14.633
Woman: Key witness in
the Whitey Bulger trial is dead.

59:14.801 --> 59:18.178
Woman 2: A source tells CNN,
authorities called the death suspicious.

59:18.346 --> 59:20.973
Man: We don't know what the cause
of death was, no sign of trauma.

59:21.140 --> 59:22.891
Don't know if this was a suicide.

59:23.059 --> 59:25.686
Man 2: lt's a very suspicious death.
And the body is seven miles away

59:25.812 --> 59:28.021
from where his automobile was,

59:28.189 --> 59:30.440
and he did not have
any identification on him.

59:31.025 --> 59:33.318
They'll probably say cause of
death was a heart attack,

59:33.486 --> 59:38.532
an aneurysm, you know, and is it?
We'll never really know.

59:38.700 --> 59:41.535
Do you believe what they tell you,
or did something really happen?

59:41.744 --> 59:45.414
Do you trust your people that are
supposed to serve and protect

59:45.582 --> 59:47.666
when you know
what we're living through,

59:47.834 --> 59:50.419
and what's happened in this family?

59:50.587 --> 59:54.423
What is the truth anymore,
and who do you believe?

01:00:00.013 --> 01:00:03.473
Sometimes, you know, l wish
that this never happened.

01:00:03.641 --> 01:00:06.560
This life... because all the hurt.

01:00:06.728 --> 01:00:09.563
l've had a lot of hurt, Joe,
l mean, from...

01:00:09.731 --> 01:00:14.985
l'm talking from... l can remember
far back as four or five years old.

01:00:16.237 --> 01:00:20.616
l don't have any faith no more.
l want the truth.

01:00:20.783 --> 01:00:23.577
This has tied me up for 32 years.

01:00:23.745 --> 01:00:26.413
They say, you know, ease your pain.

01:00:26.623 --> 01:00:32.544
And honestly, Joe, l got to tell you this,
and l say it with my throat,

01:00:32.712 --> 01:00:35.297
l'd kill this cocksucker
if they ever let him go free,

01:00:35.465 --> 01:00:37.466
and l'd tell the...

01:00:40.261 --> 01:00:44.806
Tell the judge that and l wouldn't
give a fuck about going away for it.

01:00:45.016 --> 01:00:48.393
This prick here is never gonna
run free, because l...

01:00:48.603 --> 01:00:50.896
l mean it, l'd take him out.

01:00:56.986 --> 01:01:00.238
Man: Prosecutors put former hit man
John Martorano on the stand

01:01:00.406 --> 01:01:03.283
to prove that Bulger's reign
was murderous.

01:01:03.451 --> 01:01:05.702
Woman: Martorano was perhaps
the most feared member

01:01:05.870 --> 01:01:07.454
of Bulger's Winter Hill Gang.

01:01:07.705 --> 01:01:11.208
...testified he was James Whitey
Bulger's chief executioner.

01:01:11.376 --> 01:01:12.751
Man: Killing was routine.

01:01:12.919 --> 01:01:15.253
ln all, Martorano
murdered at least 20 people.

01:01:15.463 --> 01:01:17.839
Woman: Martorano served
just 12 years in prison

01:01:18.007 --> 01:01:20.425
as part of a deal
with federal prosecutors.

01:01:20.593 --> 01:01:22.928
Man 2: The confessed murderer
was asked about a number of killings

01:01:23.096 --> 01:01:26.264
he committed, including
the killing of Roger Wheeler,

01:01:26.432 --> 01:01:28.975
the president of World Jai-Alai,
in Oklahoma.

01:01:30.520 --> 01:01:34.564
Boeri: The Jai Alai murders are
the heart of this, because they show

01:01:34.732 --> 01:01:37.984
how ugly and sordid
everything became.

01:01:38.152 --> 01:01:42.948
This is shocking. He is killed
in daylight, at a country club,

01:01:43.116 --> 01:01:45.909
while kids at the swimming pool
are watching.

01:01:46.953 --> 01:01:48.203
Wyshak: And who was Roger Wheeler?

01:01:48.371 --> 01:01:51.331
Martorano: He was the owner of Jai Alai,
World Jai Alai... it was a game.

01:01:51.499 --> 01:01:53.166
Wyshak: Did that game
involve gambling?

01:01:53.334 --> 01:01:54.918
Martorano: Yes.

01:01:55.086 --> 01:01:58.672
Man: l never did like gambling.
But the Bank of Boston

01:01:58.840 --> 01:02:00.799
brought him this Jai Alai deal.

01:02:01.050 --> 01:02:04.177
And part of the deal,
because l kept asking him about this,

01:02:04.387 --> 01:02:07.889
he said that the FBl
keeps it clean.

01:02:08.099 --> 01:02:12.018
lt's run by retired FBl agents
that specialized

01:02:12.270 --> 01:02:15.981
in investigating organized crime,
and they keep the Mob out.

01:02:16.190 --> 01:02:19.109
Boeri: So, Wheeler buys this company,
World Jai Alai.

01:02:19.235 --> 01:02:23.155
Unbeknownst to him, it's infiltrated
by the Mob already,

01:02:23.322 --> 01:02:24.865
connected to Winter Hill.

01:02:25.032 --> 01:02:28.285
Weeks: World Jai Alai
hired John Callahan,

01:02:28.453 --> 01:02:30.871
a friend of John Martorano,
as a president.

01:02:31.080 --> 01:02:34.166
And they had H. Paul Rico
head of security.

01:02:34.292 --> 01:02:37.586
And Rico was a corrupt
ex-FBl agent, and he had

01:02:37.754 --> 01:02:40.088
and he had relationships
with Winter Hill.

01:02:40.256 --> 01:02:45.302
Callahan is actually the architect who
first brought the scheme forward with Rico,

01:02:45.470 --> 01:02:49.181
to kill Wheeler, and then
go to his widow and buy it,

01:02:49.390 --> 01:02:51.767
buy World Jai Alai,
they would be the owners,

01:02:51.851 --> 01:02:54.436
and the money was going to be
kicked back to Winter Hill.

01:02:54.562 --> 01:02:58.482
Paul Rico'd resell it to the people back
up here that he was involved with before.

01:02:58.649 --> 01:03:00.776
Martorano: Callahan... he asked me to
take out Roger Wheeler.

01:03:00.943 --> 01:03:02.527
Wyshak: What was
your reaction to that?

01:03:02.695 --> 01:03:04.613
Martorano: l couldn't do that
without everybody else on board.

01:03:04.906 --> 01:03:07.449
Wyshak: And when you said you had
to get everybody else on board,

01:03:07.617 --> 01:03:08.533
who did you mean?

01:03:08.701 --> 01:03:11.661
Martorano: Whitey and Stevie.
They said they were on board,

01:03:11.829 --> 01:03:14.581
whatever they could do
to help, they'd help.

01:03:14.749 --> 01:03:18.752
Weeks: ln the end of it, John
Martorano shot Wheeler in the head.

01:03:24.926 --> 01:03:29.012
Cullen: There were honest FBl agents
in Oklahoma who wanted to get to

01:03:29.180 --> 01:03:31.348
the bottom of the murder
of Roger Wheeler.

01:03:31.516 --> 01:03:35.685
Whitey Bulger and Stevie Flemmi
were implicated, and the FBl in Boston

01:03:35.853 --> 01:03:40.023
lied to the FBl in Oklahoma.
They said Bulger and Flemmi

01:03:40.107 --> 01:03:43.485
had nothing to do with it,
they have alibis, we've checked it out.

01:03:43.653 --> 01:03:47.113
That was a lie. And murderers
went free because of it.

01:03:49.867 --> 01:03:53.662
Man: You hold the FBl
as responsible as Bulger

01:03:53.788 --> 01:03:54.913
for the death of your father?

01:03:55.122 --> 01:03:59.042
More responsible.
The FBl has protected him,

01:03:59.293 --> 01:04:01.378
they have supervised him,

01:04:01.504 --> 01:04:06.216
and without the FBl,
my father would be alive today.

01:04:08.594 --> 01:04:13.348
Next person that emerges
in this story is Brian Halloran.

01:04:13.516 --> 01:04:17.310
Halloran is facing his own problems,
namely he's charged

01:04:17.478 --> 01:04:19.437
with murdering a drug dealer.

01:04:19.647 --> 01:04:22.774
He needs help.
And this is the typical system

01:04:23.025 --> 01:04:25.360
of informants
and cooperating witnesses,

01:04:25.528 --> 01:04:28.613
he wants to make a deal.
And so he comes forward,

01:04:28.781 --> 01:04:32.117
and he can give up Whitey Bulger
and Stephen Flemmi he says,

01:04:32.285 --> 01:04:35.662
because they were part of a plot
to kill Roger Wheeler.

01:04:35.830 --> 01:04:38.957
So, Halloran is a threat
to Bulger and Flemmi.

01:04:39.125 --> 01:04:42.377
They eliminate Halloran,
and in the process of eliminating him,

01:04:42.545 --> 01:04:45.881
they kill Michael Donahue,

01:04:46.090 --> 01:04:48.550
somebody he knew
from the neighborhood.

01:04:50.052 --> 01:04:52.262
Woman: Of the 19
alleged murder victims,

01:04:52.430 --> 01:04:55.432
their loved ones have become
fixtures at this trial and today,

01:04:55.600 --> 01:04:57.809
Patricia Donahue took the stand.

01:04:57.977 --> 01:05:00.770
Donahue: All l want to do is clear
my husband's name.

01:05:00.938 --> 01:05:06.109
l did not want him associated with
the Mafia, with Whitey Bulger,

01:05:06.277 --> 01:05:08.069
with Brian Halloran.

01:05:08.237 --> 01:05:11.907
You know, he wasn't into that, he
didn't even know those people.

01:05:12.074 --> 01:05:15.869
He was innocent,
he wasn't in trouble,

01:05:16.037 --> 01:05:19.247
he wasn't a Mafia man,
he wasn't a killer.

01:05:19.415 --> 01:05:22.375
Mike was 32 when he died.

01:05:22.501 --> 01:05:25.503
He actually would've
been 33 in a week.

01:05:27.131 --> 01:05:30.967
Whitey pulled the trigger,
but l blame the FBl, too.

01:05:31.135 --> 01:05:33.219
They knew what was gonna happen.

01:05:34.138 --> 01:05:35.013
( sirens in distance )

01:05:35.139 --> 01:05:36.222
There goes Whitey.

01:05:36.349 --> 01:05:37.682
- ( woman laughing )
- That's funny.

01:05:37.850 --> 01:05:41.603
- l'm serious, lookit.
- Woman: There's Whitey, people.

01:05:42.188 --> 01:05:45.148
We'll see you in there, you lowlife.

01:05:47.276 --> 01:05:50.695
Man: Michael Donahue was murdered
simply because he offered

01:05:50.821 --> 01:05:53.365
a neighbor, Brian Halloran,
a ride home.

01:05:53.532 --> 01:05:55.909
Unbeknownst to Michael Donahue,

01:05:56.077 --> 01:06:00.246
Brian Halloran at the time
was cooperating with the FBl,

01:06:00.456 --> 01:06:04.793
and was about to reveal
that James Bulger was involved

01:06:04.961 --> 01:06:07.671
in the murder of Roger Wheeler.

01:06:08.339 --> 01:06:11.466
Fitzpatrick: After the
Wheeler murder, Halloran comes in,

01:06:11.634 --> 01:06:15.387
and he wants to talk.
We open him up as an informant,

01:06:15.554 --> 01:06:20.892
and he begins telling us that this
was done by Bulger and Flemmi.

01:06:21.060 --> 01:06:25.355
And so, l opened up murder cases
on Bulger and Flemmi.

01:06:26.357 --> 01:06:28.024
Now you have to understand
something here.

01:06:28.192 --> 01:06:31.569
Halloran is giving us the subject.

01:06:31.737 --> 01:06:35.699
He's telling us this guy
is the killer of Wheeler,

01:06:35.866 --> 01:06:40.704
Bulger is the killer of Wheeler.
That's a plus, that's a big plus.

01:06:40.871 --> 01:06:43.999
They should be very happy,
they being the Department of Justice

01:06:44.208 --> 01:06:47.252
and the Strike Force Chief
Jerry O'Sullivan.

01:06:47.420 --> 01:06:49.504
And yet, they're not.

01:06:49.672 --> 01:06:53.591
O'Sullivan said,
"No, l'm not gonna put Halloran

01:06:53.718 --> 01:06:55.552
in a witness protection program."

01:06:55.720 --> 01:06:57.012
Why not?

01:06:57.138 --> 01:06:58.930
So l went over O'Sullivan's head.

01:06:59.098 --> 01:07:01.725
l went to the United
States Attorney, Bill Weld.

01:07:01.892 --> 01:07:05.645
And l said to Bill Weld,
"Bill, we got a problem.

01:07:05.855 --> 01:07:10.316
l got an informant, Halloran, that's
gonna tell us who did this stuff.

01:07:10.484 --> 01:07:13.028
And O'Sullivan is feeling
that he should not be

01:07:13.195 --> 01:07:14.779
in the Witness Protection program."

01:07:14.947 --> 01:07:17.907
l told Weld, he's gonna get whacked.

01:07:18.117 --> 01:07:23.121
At the same time, John Morris
at the FBl, told John Connolly

01:07:23.289 --> 01:07:27.042
that Brian Halloran was
revealing Bulger's involvement.

01:07:27.209 --> 01:07:29.627
And Morris knew full well
that John Connolly

01:07:29.837 --> 01:07:33.214
would convey that information
to Whitey Bulger. And he did.

01:07:35.051 --> 01:07:38.011
Weeks: We received word from the FBl
that Brian Halloran

01:07:38.220 --> 01:07:40.680
was cooperating with the FBl
about the Wheeler murder.

01:07:40.848 --> 01:07:44.601
So Jim Bulger and Steve Flemmi,
myself and other people

01:07:44.769 --> 01:07:46.019
go out looking for him.

01:07:46.187 --> 01:07:50.607
One day we got word that Brian
Halloran was down the waterfront.

01:07:50.816 --> 01:07:53.777
Michael Donahue happened to
have gone down to the pier

01:07:53.944 --> 01:07:57.280
in South Boston to get fish
to use as bait

01:07:57.448 --> 01:08:02.118
to take one of his sons on a fishing trip.
And he stopped to have a beer

01:08:02.286 --> 01:08:06.956
on his way home. He ran into
Brian Halloran who was his neighbor.

01:08:07.124 --> 01:08:09.292
He offered to give him a ride home.

01:08:09.460 --> 01:08:11.836
So we went down the waterfront,
you know,

01:08:11.962 --> 01:08:15.757
we got the hit car, weapons,
and everyone, you know.

01:08:15.925 --> 01:08:17.634
He was geared up and stuff.
And l went down ahead,

01:08:17.760 --> 01:08:19.551
l sat across the street and watched

01:08:19.720 --> 01:08:21.845
to make sure Brian Halloran
was, in fact, there.

01:08:22.014 --> 01:08:24.890
You know, when he started
coming out, l told Jim Bulger,

01:08:25.059 --> 01:08:28.310
and Jim Bulger pulled up, and he shot
Brian Halloran and killed him.

01:08:29.729 --> 01:08:32.398
Michael Donahue
was an unintended victim.

01:08:32.566 --> 01:08:36.111
He wasn't supposed to be
getting killed, it was Brian Halloran

01:08:36.278 --> 01:08:39.113
that we were going to kill.
But he hung around with Halloran.

01:08:39.281 --> 01:08:41.698
You want to hang around
with gangsters and wise guys,

01:08:41.867 --> 01:08:43.576
this is what happens.

01:08:46.205 --> 01:08:50.166
Woman: Patricia Donahue has spent
the last 32 years raising three sons

01:08:50.376 --> 01:08:51.876
without her husband Michael.

01:08:52.044 --> 01:08:55.964
Today she finally faced his alleged killer,
James Whitey Bulger.

01:08:57.299 --> 01:09:01.051
Donahue: lt was Mother's Day, and Tommy
had just made his first Communion.

01:09:01.178 --> 01:09:05.180
l was in the kitchen cooking.
A news bulletin came on the TV

01:09:05.349 --> 01:09:08.017
about a gangland slaying.
l didn't pay any attention to it,

01:09:08.185 --> 01:09:09.935
because l knew it didn't
concern me.

01:09:10.145 --> 01:09:13.356
And l just so happened to look up
and see the car.

01:09:13.482 --> 01:09:16.901
And l said, "l think that was his car."
l mean, l was hyperventilating,

01:09:17.069 --> 01:09:19.319
l was, like, confused.

01:09:19.488 --> 01:09:21.823
l'm thinking, "Oh my God,
where is he?

01:09:21.991 --> 01:09:24.783
l need to be with him,
l don't want him to die alone,

01:09:24.910 --> 01:09:28.621
l have so much stuff l want
to say to him," you know?

01:09:28.788 --> 01:09:32.125
And, nobody came
until ten o'clock that night.

01:09:32.334 --> 01:09:34.836
So when they took me
to the hospital finally,

01:09:34.920 --> 01:09:36.712
he had already passed.

01:09:37.548 --> 01:09:40.550
Within days of the killing, FBl agents,
they came to my house

01:09:40.676 --> 01:09:45.305
and harassed me. Accused me of having
an affair with my husband's friend

01:09:45.430 --> 01:09:47.557
that was staying with us
from out of town.

01:09:47.725 --> 01:09:51.394
l mean, l was like," What?"
For months, they used to sit

01:09:51.562 --> 01:09:54.856
outside my salon, you know.
They'd sit outside the house

01:09:55.024 --> 01:09:56.983
and l'd say, "How you doing,
have you found out

01:09:57.109 --> 01:09:58.735
any more information on my husband?"

01:09:58.903 --> 01:10:03.781
"No, nothing yet."
And the whole time they knew.

01:10:03.949 --> 01:10:06.576
And l was devastated
because l did not think

01:10:06.744 --> 01:10:08.870
that the government was like that.

01:10:10.080 --> 01:10:11.080
You know, you think you know them,

01:10:11.248 --> 01:10:14.292
and you find out they're
not who you think they are.

01:10:15.711 --> 01:10:17.921
Murphy: Bulger and Flemmi
are suspects,

01:10:18.047 --> 01:10:20.131
now, not only in the Wheeler murder,

01:10:20.257 --> 01:10:22.258
but in the Halloran
and Donahue murders.

01:10:22.468 --> 01:10:27.305
And nothing happens. The FBl
decides to look for John Callahan,

01:10:27.473 --> 01:10:30.099
"We need to question John Callahan,
he's the other guy

01:10:30.267 --> 01:10:33.186
who was also implicated
in the murder of Roger Wheeler."

01:10:33.354 --> 01:10:37.106
They're hunting for him to question him,
and then he's murdered.

01:10:38.359 --> 01:10:41.778
Again, nothing happens.
The FBl in Boston,

01:10:41.946 --> 01:10:44.697
who do they send out to question
Bulger and Flemmi?

01:10:44.865 --> 01:10:47.075
John Connolly. Their handler.

01:10:47.243 --> 01:10:49.494
Because we know he's objective, right?

01:10:52.248 --> 01:10:54.916
The FBl,
they haven't been on our side

01:10:55.042 --> 01:10:57.377
since the day they killed my father.

01:10:57.586 --> 01:11:00.838
Took them four and a half hours
to come to my house to tell my mother,

01:11:01.006 --> 01:11:03.883
my mother,
whether my father was dead or alive.

01:11:04.051 --> 01:11:06.761
They covered up
the murder of my father,

01:11:06.929 --> 01:11:11.516
helped pretty much set it up.
lt's, it's, it's shameful, it's shameful.

01:11:11.684 --> 01:11:13.768
l think the FBl is
worse than the Mafia.

01:11:13.936 --> 01:11:16.729
They're the most organized
crime family on the planet,

01:11:16.981 --> 01:11:19.899
who can do whatever they want,
change the laws when they want,

01:11:20.067 --> 01:11:22.235
and they're not to be screwed with,
to be honest with you.

01:11:22.403 --> 01:11:24.904
We've seen that first-hand.

01:11:25.656 --> 01:11:28.491
Woman: Tell us what it was like
to be on the stand today

01:11:28.701 --> 01:11:31.160
and look into Whitey Bulger's eyes.

01:11:31.328 --> 01:11:34.455
Well, l looked right at him,
but of course he wouldn't look at me,

01:11:34.665 --> 01:11:36.916
so as far as l'm concerned,
he's a coward.

01:11:37.084 --> 01:11:41.379
He can kill people and not look the
victims in the face, that's a coward.

01:11:41.547 --> 01:11:42.588
That's a coward.

01:11:42.756 --> 01:11:45.842
You've been saying you're getting
more answers from his defense team--

01:11:46.051 --> 01:11:47.844
l am, l am.

01:11:48.012 --> 01:11:49.887
And then Jay Carney comes up,
and he asks you questions

01:11:50.014 --> 01:11:52.432
that are really meant
to benefit Whitey.

01:11:52.558 --> 01:11:54.726
Does that put you
in a strange position?

01:11:54.852 --> 01:11:56.686
The questions that Carney
was asking my mother,

01:11:56.854 --> 01:11:59.814
those are questions the government
should be asking my mother.

01:11:59.982 --> 01:12:03.985
Did you notice the government stood up
and blocked every question they asked.

01:12:04.111 --> 01:12:07.947
They don't want us to know anything.
lt was blunt, right there.

01:12:08.115 --> 01:12:09.949
Carney was asking questions
to help us,

01:12:10.117 --> 01:12:12.827
and we were getting blocked
by the prosecution.

01:12:12.995 --> 01:12:15.121
Where do we go here, folks?

01:12:19.460 --> 01:12:23.546
Kelly: ln the early 90s, when Fred and l
first started working on this case,

01:12:23.756 --> 01:12:29.260
it was strange to us, to say the least,
that this individual, Bulger,

01:12:29.470 --> 01:12:32.305
had been allowed to run amok
in the city of Boston for so long.

01:12:32.514 --> 01:12:35.850
We suspected, as did many
other people in law enforcement,

01:12:36.018 --> 01:12:39.395
that Bulger had some relationship
with the FBl

01:12:39.605 --> 01:12:41.230
that was...

01:12:41.398 --> 01:12:46.903
He was using to prevent
prosecution of himself.

01:12:47.071 --> 01:12:53.076
lt was in that atmosphere that we
began the case, and targeted him.

01:12:53.243 --> 01:12:57.580
And we worked with Tom Foley,
also Tom Duffy from the state police,

01:12:57.748 --> 01:12:59.665
who were very savvy investigators.

01:13:01.043 --> 01:13:04.212
So what we decided to do was follow
the money, and we started targeting

01:13:04.421 --> 01:13:08.966
a bottom line bookmaker
with some of the informants that we had.

01:13:09.093 --> 01:13:11.594
We put up a bunch of wiretaps,
and we started climbing up

01:13:11.762 --> 01:13:13.679
these bookmakers' organizations.

01:13:13.847 --> 01:13:17.266
We went from low to mid,
up to the higher level bookmaker,

01:13:17.476 --> 01:13:22.605
until we actually had the highest level,
where that bookmaker was doing

01:13:22.731 --> 01:13:26.901
the hand-off to Bulger and Flemmi
as far as payments go.

01:13:27.069 --> 01:13:31.280
lt took Brian and l about
four or five years to get there.

01:13:31.448 --> 01:13:36.160
By 1995, we had our first
racketeering indictment.

01:13:36.328 --> 01:13:40.039
Back then, Fred took a lot of
hits over the years,

01:13:40.207 --> 01:13:44.585
and we had the courage to go up
against the system, Brian Kelly too.

01:13:44.753 --> 01:13:50.216
There was many, right inside the US
Attorney's office, that were in denial,

01:13:50.426 --> 01:13:54.011
didn't want to see this
come forward. And they said,

01:13:54.179 --> 01:13:57.348
"Well, we're going to wait, we'll do
a joint investigation with the FBl."

01:13:57.516 --> 01:14:01.144
And l knew at that time
that this was another stall tactic.

01:14:01.311 --> 01:14:05.064
And l told them that, l said,
"Okay, if that's the way

01:14:05.232 --> 01:14:08.985
you want to go, but the state
police's position publicly

01:14:09.153 --> 01:14:13.406
will be you had the opportunity to
indict him and you didn't indict him."

01:14:13.574 --> 01:14:16.367
So, they went back and they had
another huddle with the US Attorney,

01:14:16.535 --> 01:14:20.163
and they said, "Okay, the indictment,
we will indict him."

01:14:20.372 --> 01:14:25.168
But they insisted that the FBl
participate in the arrest.

01:14:25.335 --> 01:14:30.173
So state police targeted Flemmi.
The FBl said they'll take Bulger.

01:14:30.340 --> 01:14:33.426
And then one night on January 5th,
we found Flemmi,

01:14:33.635 --> 01:14:37.263
and we arrested him
on the streets of Boston.

01:14:37.431 --> 01:14:42.518
And we arrested that same weekend,
John Martorano down in Florida.

01:14:42.686 --> 01:14:46.856
And we notified the FBl,
"Okay, grab Bulger."

01:14:47.024 --> 01:14:49.692
And, uh... that was the end of that.

01:14:50.569 --> 01:14:53.613
They never had Bulger,
didn't know where he was.

01:14:53.822 --> 01:14:58.493
And it was 16 years later before we
saw James Whitey Bulger again.

01:15:06.376 --> 01:15:09.879
We expected that he was tipped
off, and we found out later that

01:15:10.047 --> 01:15:15.176
that's what actually had happened.
One of the FBl agents in Boston

01:15:15.385 --> 01:15:18.387
told John Connolly that
the indictments were coming down,

01:15:18.555 --> 01:15:21.849
and he passed the information
along to Bulger.

01:15:24.561 --> 01:15:28.773
After months of sitting in jail,
Stephen Flemmi realized the FBl

01:15:28.982 --> 01:15:31.692
and John Connolly were not
coming to his rescue, and he

01:15:31.818 --> 01:15:35.947
and he decided to out himself
and Bulger's FBl informants.

01:15:37.324 --> 01:15:40.034
l'll never forget, when he
said he was an informant.

01:15:40.285 --> 01:15:43.204
l went up to visit him the next day,
or a day later, l said to him,

01:15:43.372 --> 01:15:46.999
l go, "Stevie, you're an informant,
you've been giving everybody up."

01:15:47.167 --> 01:15:51.629
And he said to me,
"Why should l do another day

01:15:51.838 --> 01:15:54.298
with all the information
l've given them people."

01:15:54.466 --> 01:15:56.676
l looked at him.
Now l'm like,

01:15:56.885 --> 01:15:58.761
"Okay, you know,
what's his next step?"

01:15:58.929 --> 01:16:01.639
You know, who's he got left
to give up?

01:16:01.807 --> 01:16:05.101
And he looked at me, he said, "Well,
we never said anything about you."

01:16:05.269 --> 01:16:08.271
So l was on the phone talking to him
through the glass.

01:16:08.397 --> 01:16:11.774
l took the phone and hung it up,
and l stood up, and l looked at him.

01:16:11.942 --> 01:16:14.485
l says, "You couldn't say anything
about me."

01:16:14.653 --> 01:16:18.406
l says, "Everything l did, l did with you."
l says, "You couldn't give me up

01:16:18.574 --> 01:16:19.949
without giving yourself up."

01:16:21.827 --> 01:16:25.288
Carney: Did you have any idea
that Flemmi was an informant

01:16:25.414 --> 01:16:28.833
until he revealed it
in a court hearing in 1999?

01:16:29.042 --> 01:16:33.129
Bulger: l didn't know that Stevie
did that there, l had no idea.

01:16:33.297 --> 01:16:35.423
And when l heard it,
l was shocked.

01:16:35.549 --> 01:16:37.258
l mean, Stevie was like my brother.

01:16:37.467 --> 01:16:41.304
l mean, l was so close to him.
He fooled me, he fooled the Mafia,

01:16:41.513 --> 01:16:44.682
he fooled Johnny, everybody.
l mean, l was shocked.

01:16:44.850 --> 01:16:47.685
l never believed he would ever do
anything like that.

01:16:47.853 --> 01:16:51.939
Did you ever have an instance
where Stevie provided

01:16:52.149 --> 01:16:54.400
some information in your presence?

01:16:54.568 --> 01:16:58.112
One time John Connolly asked him
a question and Stevie answered,

01:16:58.280 --> 01:17:01.824
he gave a name. When l heard that
l brought the thing to a close,

01:17:01.992 --> 01:17:03.701
and l told Steve, "C'mon, let's go."

01:17:03.869 --> 01:17:06.287
And l start hollering at him
as we went down the stairs,

01:17:06.413 --> 01:17:08.873
l told him,
"What the fuck did you do that for?"

01:17:09.082 --> 01:17:13.210
l says, "We're paying, we're not saying.
We're buying, we're not selling."

01:17:14.421 --> 01:17:17.048
Brennan: When Stephen Flemmi came out
and said he was an informant

01:17:17.257 --> 01:17:20.009
and was granted immunity,
the government wanted to shut him up,

01:17:20.218 --> 01:17:22.553
and John Connolly made the mistake
of coming in

01:17:22.721 --> 01:17:26.140
and taking Steve Flemmi's side and
saying, "We did give him immunity.

01:17:26.308 --> 01:17:30.436
The entire D.O.J. did it, you knew we were
doing it, that's what you told us to do.

01:17:30.604 --> 01:17:33.189
You paid us to do it,
you gave us bonuses to do it."

01:17:33.315 --> 01:17:35.816
At that point, the federal government
was either going to have to expose

01:17:36.026 --> 01:17:38.110
all the corruptness
in the federal government,

01:17:38.320 --> 01:17:41.781
all the murders, or they have to say
